## Monitoring Pipeline

### Reference Windows

| Data Type | Reference Window | Comparison Window | Frequency |
|-----------|-----------------|-------------------|-----------|
| Training data | Full training set | Last 24 hours | Hourly |
| Feature statistics | Last 30 days | Last 24 hours | Daily |
| Predictions | Last 7 days | Last 24 hours | Daily |

### Alerting Thresholds

| Signal | Warning | Critical | Action |
|--------|---------|----------|--------|
| Feature PSI | > 0.10 | > 0.25 | Investigate / Retrain |
| Prediction distribution KS | p < 0.01 | p < 0.001 | Investigate |
| Missing values increase | > 5% | > 20% | Check upstream |
| Schema violation | Any | Any | Block pipeline |

---

## Retraining Triggers

### Automatic Retraining

Trigger automatic retraining when:
- [ ] PSI > threshold for any critical feature
- [ ] Model performance drops below acceptable threshold
- [ ] Scheduled periodic retraining interval reached
- [ ] New labeled data exceeds minimum batch size

### Manual Retraining

Require manual investigation when:
- [ ] Multiple features drift simultaneously (possible upstream issue)
- [ ] Concept drift detected (performance drops without feature drift)
- [ ] Schema changes in upstream data

---

## Implementation Checklist

- [ ] Reference distributions stored for all features used by the model
- [ ] Drift detection runs on a schedule (at least daily)
- [ ] Alerts configured for warning and critical thresholds
- [ ] Dashboard shows drift metrics over time
- [ ] Retraining pipeline can be triggered manually or automatically
- [ ] Drift events are logged with timestamp and affected features
